<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-12-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-12-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="381" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d381">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72119/8217½</note>
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mrs. <persName type="from">Woodrow Wilson</persName> to
                            the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-12-01">December 1, 1919</date>.]</dateline></opener>
                    <p>The President wishes me to say he adheres to his original decision in regard
                        to the withdrawing of our American Commissioners.</p>
                    <closer><signed>E. B. W[<hi rend="smallcaps">ilson</hi>]</signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>